Part 5: Labels and ReplicaSets

ReplicaSet example:

selector:
  matchLabels:
    app: nginx

Pod:

labels:
  app: nginx

ReplicaSet finds Pod because:

Selector = Label

If Pod label changes:

labels:
  app: apache

ReplicaSet no longer manages that Pod.

Lab

Change label:

kubectl label pod nginx-pod app=apache --overwrite

Observe ReplicaSet behavior.

Part 6: Labels and Deployments

Deployment:

selector:
  matchLabels:
    app: nginx

Pod Template:

labels:
  app: nginx

Must match.

Bad Example

selector:
  matchLabels:
    app: nginx

Pod:

labels:
  app: apache

Deployment fails.

Troubleshoot:

kubectl describe deployment
Part 7: Labels and Services

This is where labels become extremely important.

Create Deployment:

labels:
  app: nginx

Service:

selector:
  app: nginx

Service discovers Pods automatically.

Architecture

Service
   |
Selector
   |
app=nginx
   |
Pods

Verify

kubectl get endpoints

Service automatically lists matching Pods.

Intermediate Scenario
Service Not Working

Application unreachable.

Check:

kubectl get endpoints

Output:

No Endpoints

Check:

kubectl get pods --show-labels
kubectl describe svc

Problem:

Pod Label:
app=nginx

Service Selector:
app=apache

Fix:

Update selector.

This is one of the most common real-world issues.

Part 8: Match Expressions

Basic:

matchLabels:
  app: nginx

Advanced:

matchExpressions:
- key: env
  operator: In
  values:
  - dev
  - qa

Meaning:

Select Pods
where env is dev OR qa

Production Example

matchExpressions:
- key: team
  operator: In
  values:
  - devops
  - sre

Useful in large clusters.

Expert Scenario 1
Banking Application

Architecture:

Internet Banking
Mobile Banking
Payment Gateway

Labels:

labels:
  app: payment-gateway
  env: prod
  team: banking
  criticality: high

Benefits:

